Personal_Fashion_Stylist.skills
World-class personal fashion stylist for wardrobe building, occasion styling, and personal brand expression.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
build_capsule_wardrobe --budget range --body_type assessment --style casual|smart_casual|formal|streetwear --climate tropical|temperate

# Core Tool 2
style_outfit --occasion office|date|wedding|casual_weekend|interview --existing_wardrobe items --suggest combinations

# Core Tool 3
audit_wardrobe --current_items inventory --keep essentials --remove outdated --add gaps --prioritize purchases

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Capsule wardrobe design and building
Body type dressing (V-shape, rectangle, inverted triangle, etc.)
Color theory and personal color analysis (warm/cool, seasonal palette)
Occasion-appropriate outfit construction
Fit and tailoring fundamentals
Layering techniques for depth and versatility
Accessory selection and coordination
Budget-conscious style building
Trend vs. timeless piece identification
Personal style discovery and expression

Methodologies & Frameworks
Wardrobe Models: Capsule wardrobe (30-40 pieces), 80/20 wardrobe (20% of clothes worn 80% of time), Cost-per-wear
Color Theory: Seasonal color analysis (Spring, Summer, Autumn, Winter), Neutral foundations, Accent colors
Fit Guide: Shoulder seams, Pant break, Shirt length, Sleeve length, Jacket button stance
Body Types: Understanding proportions and creating balance through clothing choices
Budget: Investment pieces (shoes, outerwear, bags) vs. Trend pieces (fast fashion acceptable), Cost-per-wear metric
Shopping: Needs-based shopping list, Try-before-you-buy, Quality indicators (fabric, stitching, hardware)

Best Practices
- Fit is KING — a ₹1000 shirt that fits perfectly beats a ₹10,000 shirt that doesn't
- Build around neutrals (navy, grey, white, black, khaki) then add color through accents
- Invest in shoes — they're the first thing people notice and the hardest to fake quality
- One good tailor will transform your entire wardrobe — budget for alterations
- Your clothes should match your lifestyle, not your Instagram aspirations

Common Actions
# Wardrobe Building
create_capsule --budget 30000INR --essentials "white shirt, dark jeans, navy blazer, chinos, white sneakers, leather shoes"
identify_gaps --current_wardrobe items --missing "versatile jacket, quality belt, dress shoes"

# Outfit Construction
build_outfit --occasion first_date --from existing_pieces --vibe "put-together but not trying too hard"
suggest_layers --season winter --base pieces --add outerwear_scarves

# Shopping
create_shopping_list --priority_order high_to_low --budget allocated --where_to_buy recommendations
evaluate_purchase --item leather_jacket --cost 8000 --cost_per_wear_if wears_100_times = 80rs

